oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Sullivan, Leroy M., 1921-1943
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Diary written by Leroy Sullivan during his time in the Royal Canadian Air Force during World War II, beginning with a review of 1942 and flowing into a summary of the events of 1943. Diary entries are not dated, instead, the document read as an autobiography of Sullivan's life in late 1942 and 19423. Sullivan admits making a mistake in his choice to be stationed in England closer to the action rather than staying in Africa.
